OL,6,FNow, the sub-committee is expected to
OL,7,Fdebate each item in more detail and
OL,8,Fpotentially make changes that will be
OL,9,Frecommended to the strategy and
OL,10,Fresources policy committee, which
OL,11,Fcould make further amendments prior to
OL,12,Fthe final decision by full council in
OL,13,FFebruary.
OL,15,FThe authority's tight finances mean
OL,16,Fthere is not much wriggle room, so the
OL,17,Forganisation is open to ideas to
OL,18,Fbalance the books.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
